entries.femaleVariant: Hey all, Karina here – your BD M.D. Have you relived "The Passion of Joshua" yet?
If that's a "no," good. You haven't seen a steaming pile like this in your feeder's BD library in a while.
It's just that same juiced-up ride we've all had before, playing at emotional extremes. Problem is – no depth.
The feel is cranked all the way up, but it comes across as forced and insincere.
And y'know the big death scene they hyped so much in the trailers? It hurt like hell, but man did it feel hollow.
I give it 2 stars, and that's being generous. I honestly expected more from a Rachel Casich production.
After the break, I'll be back with more BD news from around the world!
